{TYPICAL IDEAS AND STRATEGIES - PART 1} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {The
Rossolimo is a rich opening containing many different strategies. The
Rossolimo is the best practical choice for White, while it's theoretically
equal to 3.d4 (which requires much more theoretical knowledge). Black has many
acceptable systems, and with this lecture, we will begin by examining the
different strategies White has at his disposal against each of them. Strategic
themes in this lecture: > Playing in the centre with c3-d4 > Doubled pawns on
the c-file > Dark square strategy > Hedgehog structure} *

