1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nd4 $2 {This is a bad move - Black is losing time
by moving the same piece twice! The move ...Nd4 may become playable at later
point.} (3... a6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. h3 Nf6 6. d3 e6 7. O-O b6) 4. Nxd4 $1 cxd4 5.
O-O {Black has several moves. However we do not need to know any theory - just
the basic plans.} (5. d3 $4 Qa5+ $19 {is a trap to avoid.}) 5... g6 6. c3 $1 ({
Another playable option is} 6. d3 a6 7. Ba4 Bg7 {Again White has a choice
between several logical moves:} 8. Nd2 {[%cal Yf2f4,Yd2f3]} (8. f4) (8. c3))
6... Bg7 (6... dxc3 7. Nxc3 a6 8. Ba4 b5 9. Bb3 e6 (9... Nf6 10. e5 $16) 10. d4
$16 {Black has misplayed the opening and White has a clear advantage.}) 7. cxd4
Bxd4 {The is misplaced on d4 since it's not secure.} 8. Nc3 Bg7 ({If, for
example} 8... a6 {then} 9. Ba4 b5 10. Bb3 Bb7 11. d3 Bg7 {and now for example}
(11... Nf6 12. Bh6) 12. Be3 ({or the more active} 12. Bg5 b4 {with the idea}
13. Nd5)) 9. d4 a6 10. Ba4 e6 11. d5 $1 {White is attacking fast and does not
allow Black to compelete his debelopment!} (11. e5 {is another interesting
idea, intending Ne4.}) 11... Ne7 12. Bf4 (12. d6 $5 {is maybe also good, but
maybe Black can play around this pawn after} Nc6) 12... O-O 13. Bd6 Re8 14. Bb3
b5 15. e5 Nxd5 $4 16. Nxd5 exd5 17. Qxd5 Ra7 18. Qxf7+ Kh8 19. Rac1 Re6 (19...
Bxe5 20. Bxe5+ Rxe5 21. Rxc8 Qxc8 22. Qf6#) 20. Bxe6 dxe6 21. Qxa7 1-0

