{An instructive game showing typical plans in the structure with doubled
c-pawns!} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 $2 {A rare (and bad) move. In several
lines White takes on c6 without being provoked.} 4. Bxc6 bxc6 5. O-O {Now
White will choose a strategy depending on Black's reply.} Nf6 (5... d6 6. c3 (
6. d4 {is playable although I would not play it.} cxd4 7. Qxd4 e5 8. Qd3 {
[%cal Yc2c4,Yb1c3]}) (6. e5 {is another typical idea but here Black's
light-squared bishop is quite strong. White is better but once the position
opens up this strategy might backfire.} dxe5 (6... d5 {[%cal Yc8f5,Yf5g4]}) (
6... Bg4) 7. Nxe5 Qc7 8. Re1 e6 9. Nc3 Bd6 10. Nf3 Ne7 11. d3 O-O) 6... Nf6 7.
Re1 g6 8. d4 {This may look surprising - White undoubles Black's pawns. Still,
d4 is strong since after taking on d4 Black remains with pawn weaknesses.} cxd4
9. cxd4 $16) 6. e5 Nd5 7. c4 Nb6 8. Qe2 e6 9. Nc3 Be7 10. d3 O-O 11. Nd2 {
White is preparing to meet ...d6 with f4. Still Nd2 looks a bit artificial.} (
11. Bd2 {- a random move, just to see what Black's idea can be:} f6 $1 ({After
} 11... d5 $2 12. b3 {[%csl Rc5,Rc6,Rc8] Black's light-squared bishop is
eternally bad.}) 12. Rfe1 fxe5 13. Nxe5 Qc7 14. Rad1 d6 15. Nf3 e5 {Suddenly
Black's c8-bishop becomes very strong.}) (11. Ne4 $1 $16) 11... d5 $2 ({
Black should try} 11... d6 12. f4 dxe5 13. fxe5 Qd4+ 14. Kh1 Rd8 15. Rf3 {
[%cal Yd2b3] White is about to stabilise his position with Nb3 with a big
advantage.}) 12. f4 {White fortifies the e5-pawn. Black's c8-bishop remains
hemmed in by his own pawns.} Bb7 13. Nf3 a5 14. a4 ({After} 14. b3 a4 15. Bd2
axb3 16. axb3 {Black is effectively playing without the bishop on b7. In the
end, the c5-pawn will be a "victim".}) 14... Qc7 15. Bd2 Rad8 16. Be1 f6 17.
Bg3 Qd7 18. Rfd1 d4 19. Ne4 f5 20. Ned2 Rde8 21. Nb3 Qc7 22. Qe1 Bd8 23. Bh4
Bxh4 24. Qxh4 Nd7 25. h3 g6 26. Qh6 Re7 27. Nbd2 Qb8 28. b3 Rg7 29. Ng5 Qe8 30.
Ndf3 Bc8 31. Kf2 Nb6 32. Rf1 Nd7 33. Ke2 Nb6 34. Kd2 Nd7 35. Rab1 Nb6 36. Rf2
Nd7 37. Nh2 Nb6 38. Ra1 Bd7 39. Rc1 Nc8 40. Rg1 Ne7 41. g4 fxg4 42. hxg4 Kh8
43. Rh1 Ng8 44. Qh4 Qe7 45. Nhf3 Bc8 46. Rfh2 Bd7 47. Qxh7+ Rxh7 48. Rxh7+ 1-0

