1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. d3 {We will play a long-term
game, since we have the better pawn structure.} ({Against 4...dxc6,} 5. c3 $2 {
is a mistake:} Qd3) 5... g6 (5... Qc7 6. a4 (6. Qd2 e5 7. Qc3 f6 8. Be3 b6 9.
a4 a5 10. Qb3 Bd6 11. Na3) 6... a5) (5... Bg4 6. h3 Bxf3 7. Qxf3 e5 8. Nd2 $16
Bd6 (8... b5 $2 {Creating a big weakness on c5.} 9. O-O Nf6 10. Nb3 $16) 9. a4
Nf6 $2 10. a5 $1 $18 {I would evaluate this position as completely winning for
White! Black's queenside pawns have been immobilised while they also can be
attacked by pieces or by pawns!}) 6. Bd2 Bg7 7. Bc3 f6 8. e5 $1 {Preventing ...
e5 - with a big advantage for White.} Bg4 9. Nbd2 fxe5 10. h3 Bxf3 11. Nxf3 Qd5
12. Qe2 Nf6 13. O-O O-O 14. Nxe5 b5 15. b3 b4 16. Bb2 Nh5 17. Qe4 Nf4 18. Rfe1
Rae8 19. Rab1 a5 20. Nxc6 Qg5 21. Kh1 Bxb2 22. Rxb2 e5 23. Rbb1 Nxh3 24. gxh3
Rxf2 25. Rg1 Qd2 26. Rg2 Qxc2 27. Rbg1 Qxa2 28. Rxg6+ Kh8 29. Qxe5+ 1-0

