1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. d3 Bg4 6. h3 Bh5 7. Nbd2 {
In these positions the knight is better on d2 than on c3. From there it can go
to c4 or f1.} Qc7 8. Nc4 e6 9. Bd2 b6 10. Qe2 Nf6 11. g4 {A good move that
could have been played even earlier.} Bg6 12. Nce5 $16 {White is much better,
however Black's next move loses immediately.} Bd6 $4 13. Nxg6 hxg6 14. e5 $18
Nxg4 15. exd6 Qxd6 16. O-O-O Nf6 17. Ng5 Qd5 18. c4 Qd6 19. Ne4 Nxe4 20. dxe4
Qe5 21. Qe3 Rh4 22. f4 Qd4 23. Qg3 Qxc4+ 24. Bc3 Rh5 25. f5 Qxa2 26. fxg6 e5
27. Qg4 Rh6 28. Qd7+ Kf8 29. Qd6+ 1-0

