1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. d3 Qc7 6. e5 Bg4 7. Bf4 e6 8. h3
Bxf3 9. Qxf3 Ne7 10. Nd2 Ng6 11. O-O (11. Bg3 $1 {would have been even better,
when e5 is indirectly protected.} Be7 (11... Nxe5 $4 12. Qh5 Bd6 13. Ne4 $18)
12. Qe3 O-O 13. O-O {What about 0-0-0 instead? This would give Black some
undeserved counterplay.} Rad8 14. a4 a5 15. f4 (15. Nc4) 15... b6 16. Kh1 $16 {
Black has zero active plans while White can continue to improve his position.})
11... f5 12. Nc4 {Here White's advantage is somewhat reduced although he still
won the game.} b5 13. Nd6+ Bxd6 14. exd6 Qd7 15. Rfe1 O-O 16. Re2 Rad8 17. Rae1
Rfe8 18. Bg5 Rc8 19. Qg3 e5 20. Rxe5 Rxe5 21. Rxe5 Nxe5 22. Qxe5 c4 23. dxc4
bxc4 24. Qd4 Rb8 25. Qxc4+ Kh8 26. Qd4 c5 27. Qe5 c4 28. Be7 Rb5 29. Qd4 h6 30.
b3 cxb3 31. axb3 Kh7 32. Qd3 Re5 33. Kh2 a5 34. Bh4 Kg8 35. Bg3 Re8 36. Qd5+
Qf7 37. Qb5 Kh7 38. Be5 f4 39. Qd3+ Kg8 40. c4 Rc8 41. Bc3 a4 42. bxa4 f3 43.
