{A great example of dark-squared strategy of the Rossolimo!} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3
Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. c3 Bg7 (4... Nf6 $1) 5. O-O Nf6 6. Re1 O-O 7. h3 (7. d4 cxd4
8. cxd4 a6 9. Bxc6 (9. Bd3 d6 10. h3 e5 11. dxe5 dxe5 12. Nc3) 9... dxc6 10. h3
Nd7 11. Nc3 e5 12. Be3 exd4 13. Bxd4 Bxd4 14. Qxd4) 7... Ne8 $2 ({Another
typical mistake is} 7... d5 $2 {Black plays the same move after 7.d4, but the
knight cannot go to e4 here!} 8. e5 Ne8 (8... Ne4 9. d3) 9. d4 cxd4 10. cxd4
Bd7 11. Nc3 e6 $2 12. Bxc6 $5 {Initiating the dark-square strategy! This is
working because Black has played ...g6 and ...e6, creating weaknesses on the
dark squares. By exchanging our bishop for Black's knight we eliminate one
defender of the dark squares.} Bxc6 13. Bf4 Qd7 14. Qd2 Rc8 15. Nh2 {The
knight is transferred to g4.} (15. Nd1) 15... h5 16. g4 hxg4 17. Nxg4 $16) ({
Black should probably play} 7... e5) 8. d4 {Natural and best.} (8. Bf1 $2 {
would be wrong since this allows} e5 $1 {, stopping d4. Now, Black has a good
position, for example} 9. d3 (9. a4 d6 10. Na3 h6 11. Nc4 Be6 12. d3 f5 $15)
9... d6 10. Nbd2 h6 $15 {[%cal Yf7f5]}) 8... cxd4 9. cxd4 d5 (9... Qb6 10. Bxc6
bxc6 11. Nc3 d6 12. Bg5) 10. e5 (10. exd5 {was also possible:} Qxd5 11. Nc3 Qd8
12. d5 Nb8 13. Bg5 Bf6 14. Bxf6 Nxf6 15. Qd4 $1 a6 16. Bc4 (16. Bf1 Nbd7 17.
Rad1 (17. Re3)) 16... b5 17. Bb3 Bb7 18. Rad1 $16) 10... Qb6 11. Nc3 e6 12.
Bxc6 $3 {Since Black has played ...e6, White initiates a dark-square strategy.}
Qxc6 ({If} 12... bxc6 {then} 13. Na4 {with a strategically winning position.} (
{or} 13. b3 Qa5 14. Na4)) 13. Qd3 {Not the best move, but not bad either.} (13.
Bg5 f6 14. exf6 Nxf6 15. Ne5 $16) 13... a6 14. b3 b5 $2 ({White would also
have the advantage after} 14... Nc7 15. Ba3 Re8 16. Rac1 $16) 15. Ba3 $18 Nc7
16. Bxf8 Bxf8 17. Rac1 Qb6 18. a4 b4 19. Ne2 Bh6 20. Rc2 Bd7 21. g4 Ne8 22. g5
Bf8 23. Nh2 Ng7 24. Ng3 Nf5 25. Ng4 Be7 26. Nxf5 exf5 27. Nf6+ Bxf6 28. gxf6
Be6 29. Qe3 Qd8 30. Qh6 Qf8 31. Qxf8+ Kxf8 32. Rec1 Ke8 33. Rc7 Kd8 34. Re7 Rc8
35. Rxc8+ Kxc8 36. Rxe6 fxe6 37. f7 1-0

