{A great example - various possible plans are included in the analysis.} 1. e4
c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. c3 Nf6 (5... a6 6. Bxc6 dxc6 (6... bxc6
7. d4 cxd4 8. cxd4 d6 9. h3 (9. Nc3 $6 Bg4 $132) 9... Nf6 10. Nc3 O-O 11. Re1
$14 (11. Bg5 h6 (11... Nd7 12. Qd2) 12. Bf4) 11... a5 12. Bf4 Ba6 13. Qd2 Nd7
14. Bh6 c5 15. Bxg7 Kxg7 16. d5 $16) 7. d3 Nf6 (7... Bg4 8. h3 Bxf3 9. Qxf3 Nf6
10. a4 a5 11. Na3 Nd7 12. Qg3 $14) (7... e5 8. Be3 b6 9. a4 a5 10. Na3 Ne7 11.
Nc4 Qc7 12. b4 $1 axb4 13. cxb4 cxb4 14. Bxb6 Qb8 15. Bc5 $18) 8. Be3 Nd7 9. d4
cxd4 10. cxd4 O-O 11. Nc3 e5 12. h3 exd4 13. Bxd4 Bxd4 14. Qxd4 $16) (5... e6
$2 6. d4 cxd4 7. cxd4 d5 8. Bxc6+ bxc6 9. e5 Ba6 10. Re1 Ne7 11. Nc3 O-O 12.
Na4 Re8 13. Nc5 Qb6 14. b3 $18) (5... e5 6. d4 cxd4 7. cxd4 exd4 8. Bf4 $13) 6.
Re1 O-O (6... O-O 7. h3 (7. d4 d5 8. e5 Ne4) 7... e5 $1 (7... d6 8. d4 cxd4 9.
cxd4 $16) (7... d5 8. e5 Ne8 9. d4 cxd4 10. cxd4 $16) (7... Qb6 8. a4 (8. Bf1
$6 e5 $11) (8. Ba4 Rd8 9. d3) 8... a6 (8... d6 9. d3) 9. Bxc6 dxc6 (9... Qxc6
10. e5 Nd5 11. d4) 10. a5 $16) 8. d4 (8. d3 Qc7 9. a3 (9. Be3) 9... d6 10. b4
a6 11. Bc4) 8... cxd4 9. cxd4 Nxd4 10. Nxd4 exd4 11. Qxd4 d5 12. e5 Ne4 13. Nc3
Nxc3 14. bxc3 $14) (6... a6 7. Bxc6 dxc6 (7... bxc6 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 d5 10.
e5 Ne4 11. Qc2 Bd7 12. Be3 O-O 13. Nbd2 $16) 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 Bg4 10. Nbd2
O-O 11. h3 Bxf3 12. Nxf3 Nd7 $14) 7. h3 d5 8. e5 Nd7 9. d4 cxd4 10. cxd4 Qb6
11. Nc3 e6 12. Bf4 ({Here, I would be sceptical about taking on c6 right away
because after} 12. Bxc6 bxc6 {Black threatens to get counterplay with ...c5.} (
12... Qxc6 {is tantamount to an admission of defeat.} 13. Bf4 Nb6 14. Rc1 Qe8
15. b3 Bd7 16. Qd2 $16 {[%cal Yf4h6,Yf3h2,Yh2g4,Yc3d1,Yd1e3,Ye3g4]}) 13. Na4
Qb5 14. b3 {Here Black can consider an exchange sacrifice:} c5 15. Ba3 cxd4)
12... a6 13. Bxc6 bxc6 14. Na4 Qb5 15. Rc1 Bb7 16. b3 {White has a
strategically winning position.} Rac8 17. Nc5 Nxc5 18. Rxc5 (18. dxc5 {Even
this is good - since the knight gets a lovely square on d4.}) 18... Qb6 19. Qd2
Qd8 ({If} 19... Rfe8 20. Rd1 Bf8 {then White can even sacrifice the rook:} 21.
Rdc1 (21. Rc2 c5) 21... Bxc5 22. Rxc5 $18 {White's attack on the black squares
cannot be stopped!}) 20. Bg5 Qd7 21. Bf6 Rfe8 22. Bxg7 Kxg7 23. Qf4 Qe7 24.
Rec1 Rf8 25. h4 h6 26. Re1 Rce8 27. Re3 f6 28. exf6+ Rxf6 29. Qe5 Kh7 30. Ng5+
Kg8 31. Nh3 Rf5 32. Qg3 Kh7 33. Nf4 Qf6 34. Rf3 g5 35. hxg5 Rxg5 36. Qh3 Reg8
37. Nxe6 Rxg2+ 38. Kf1 Qg6 39. Nf4 Qb1+ 40. Ke2 Re8+ 41. Kd2 1-0

