1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 e6 4. O-O Nge7 5. Re1 ({White can also go for the
hedgehog setup with} 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 Qb6 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. Bd3 Ng6 9. c4 $14)
5... a6 6. Bf1 (6. Bxc6 Nxc6 7. d4 {is another way to play which was
fashionable 20 years ago. I don't suggest this since computers have found
reliable defences.}) 6... g6 $2 {Playing ...g6 is good. Playing ...e6 is good.
But playing both, is not good!} 7. d4 $1 (7. c3 $1 $16 Bg7 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4
d5 10. e5 O-O 11. Nc3 Bd7 12. Bf4 $16 ({If it were possible} 12. Bb5 {could be
played, initiating a dark-square strategy.} Rc8 13. Bxc6 Nxc6 14. Bg5 Qb6 15.
Qd2 Na5 16. b3 Nc6 17. Rac1 $16)) 7... cxd4 8. Nxd4 Bg7 9. Nxc6 Nxc6 10. c4 $16
d6 (10... O-O 11. Nc3 (11. Qd6 $5) {We surely do not need to fear} 11... Bxc3
$2 12. bxc3 $18 {when all the black squares in Black's position are weak.}) 11.
Nc3 O-O 12. Be3 Qc7 13. Rc1 Bd7 14. Re2 $5 (14. Qd2 $16 {would be more common.}
) 14... f5 {In 99.9% of the cases this move is answered by} 15. exf5 {when
Black remains with too many weaknesses.} gxf5 16. f4 $16 Be8 17. Rd2 Rd8 18.
Na4 Qe7 19. Nb6 Bf7 20. Qf3 Kh8 21. Rcd1 Rfe8 22. Qf2 Bg6 23. a3 e5 24. Nd5 Qf7
25. Bb6 Rc8 26. b4 Nd4 27. a4 Qg8 28. a5 Bf7 29. Ne3 Be6 30. Kh1 Qf7 31. Bd3
Rf8 32. Bf1 Rfe8 33. Kg1 Rg8 34. Bxd4 exd4 35. Rxd4 Bxd4 36. Rxd4 Rcd8 37. Qd2
Qe7 38. Be2 Rgf8 39. Bf3 Rfe8 40. g3 Rf8 41. Kf2 Rfe8 42. Bg2 Rf8 43. Qd3 Qc7
44. Bh3 b6 45. Bxf5 Bxf5 46. Nxf5 Rf6 47. axb6 Qxb6 48. c5 Qc6 49. Nxd6 Qh1 50.
Nf7+ Kg7 51. Nxd8 Qxh2+ 52. Ke1 Qg2 53. Rd7+ Kf8 54. Rd6 1-0

