{TYPICAL IDEAS AND STRATEGIES - PART 2} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {In this
lecture, we continue to examine typical strategic ideas. We begin by studying
positions with doubled c-pawns in more detail. Strategic themes in this
lecture: > Doubled pawns on the c-file > Playing against Black's light-squared
bishop after exchanging on c6 > When to play e4-e5 > Semi-dark-square strategy}
*

