1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 e6 4. Bxc6 bxc6 5. d3 d5 $1 (5... d6 {[%cal Ye6e5]})
(5... Ne7 {[%cal Ye7g6,Ye6e5]}) 6. Nbd2 Nf6 7. Qe2 Be7 8. c4 O-O 9. b3 (9. Ne5
{with the idea f4 also makes sense.} Qc7 10. f4 Nd7 11. Ndf3 Nxe5 {Now White
can even play} 12. fxe5 $5 {, keeping Black's c8-bishop locked in.} dxc4 13.
dxc4 $16) 9... Qc7 10. O-O $6 (10. Bb2 $1) 10... Nh5 ({Black should have taken
her chance to play} 10... e5 $3 11. exd5 cxd5 12. Qxe5 Bd6 $132) 11. e5 f5 12.
g3 g6 13. Nb1 $3 {White has regained control of the position.} f4 14. g4 Ng7
15. Nc3 $18 Qd8 16. Ba3 h5 17. h3 hxg4 18. hxg4 Kf7 19. Kg2 Bd7 20. Na4 Rh8 21.
Bxc5 (21. Rh1 {was even better in my opinion.}) 21... Qf8 22. d4 Bxc5 23. Nxc5
{White has won a pawn while keeping all the advantages of her position.
Black's light-squared bishop is still passive.} Rd8 24. Qd2 g5 25. Nxg5+ Ke7
26. Rh1 Nf5 27. Qxf4 Nh4+ 28. Kg3 Qxf4+ 29. Kxf4 Rdf8+ 30. Kg3 1-0

