1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. c3 a6 (5... Nf6 6. Re1 a6 $6 7.
Bxc6 dxc6 8. d3 $1 (8. d4 {allows} cxd4 9. cxd4 Bg4 $1 {getting rid of the
inactive c8-bishop.}) (8. h3 $5) 8... O-O ({After} 8... Bg4 9. h3 Bxf3 10. Qxf3
$14 {the difference to 8.d4 is that White does not have a pawn on d4 which
could be attacked.} O-O 11. Qe2 Nd7 12. Be3 e5 13. a4 a5 14. Na3) 9. h3 Qc7 $2
{SUPER SOS! Now Black is much worse because after 1...Qc7 2.e5 Nd5 White has 3.
c4!!+/- and ...Nb4 is no longer possible because of a3!} (9... Nd7 10. Be3 $1
$14 {check out the plan with Be3-Nbd2-Qc2 and...b4!} (10. Qc2 $14) (10. Bg5 $1
$14) 10... e5 11. Qc2 Re8 12. Nbd2 Qc7 (12... Qe7 13. a4 a5 14. Rad1 b6 15. d4
$14) 13. b4 $3 $16) (9... Re8 10. e5) 10. e5 $3 Nd7 (10... Nd5 11. c4 Nb6 (
11... Nb4 12. a3) 12. Bf4 Rd8 13. Qe2 Bf5 14. Rd1 $1 Nd7 15. g4 Be6 16. Nc3 $18
) 11. Bf4 $1 Nb6 12. c4 Bf5 13. g4 $1 Be6 14. Nc3 Rad8 15. Qe2 $18) 6. Bxc6
dxc6 (6... bxc6 7. d4 cxd4 8. cxd4 d6 9. h3 $14 ({But not} 9. Nc3 Bg4 $1 $132 {
and Black activates his bishop. For example} 10. Be3 Nf6 11. h3 Bxf3 12. Qxf3
O-O 13. Rfd1 Nd7) 9... Nf6 10. Nc3 O-O 11. Re1 (11. Bf4) 11... Nd7 12. Bf4 {
Provoking ...e5 to give Black a permanent weakness.} e5 13. dxe5 dxe5 14. Be3
$16) 7. d3 $1 (7. h3 $1 {with the idea d2-d4 is also good.}) 7... Nf6 (7... e5
$2 {At a first glance Black is doing well when in reality he is almost lost!
The temp lost by playing ...a6 makes itself felt.} 8. a4 a5 {Black should
never permit a5.} (8... Ne7 $2 9. a5 $18 O-O 10. Be3 Qd6 11. Na3 {and if} Be6 {
then simply} 12. Nc4 Bxc4 13. dxc4 $18 {and the pawn on c5 will soon drop.}) 9.
Na3 $1 Ne7 10. Be3 b6 11. Nc4 Bg4 (11... Qc7 12. b4 $1 $18 axb4 13. cxb4 cxb4
14. Bxb6 Qb8 15. Bc5 {and Black can resign.}) 12. h3 Bxf3 13. Qxf3 O-O 14. Qg3
f6 15. Rfd1 $16) (7... Bg4 8. h3 Bxf3 9. Qxf3 Nf6 10. a4 a5 11. Na3 Nd7 12. Qg3
$5 (12. Qe2 e5 (12... O-O 13. f4 $16) 13. Be3 O-O 14. f3 $1 Re8 15. Qf2 b6 16.
Nc4 $14 {and we'll try for d4, b4, or f4!}) 12... O-O 13. f4 $16 Nb6 (13... e5
14. f5) 14. Nc2) 8. h3 O-O (8... Nd7 9. Be3 (9. Bg5 $5 $16) 9... O-O (9... e5
10. d4 $16) 10. d4 $16 cxd4 11. cxd4 c5 12. Nc3 cxd4 13. Nxd4 $1 (13. Bxd4 $14)
13... Nb6 (13... Ne5 14. Qe2 $16) 14. b3 Bd7 15. Qd2 $16) 9. Qc2 $1 {this is
the key move (after h3)  ...the idea is to prepare d3-d4 ...sometimes even
b2-b4!} (9. Re1 $1 {transposing to the line with 5...Nf6 and 6...a6} Qc7 $2 (
9... Nd7 10. Bg5 (10. Be3)) 10. e5) 9... Qc7 10. Be3 b6 11. d4 $5 $14 (11. Rd1
e5 12. Nbd2 Nd7 13. b4 $16) *

