{An amazing strategical achievment by White! White got a winning position
after the great move 14.b4!! Black was left with absolutely no plan and was
left playing for tricks.} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. Re1 (5.
c3 $1 e5 $6 6. d4 $1) 5... Nf6 (5... e5 $1 6. b4 $5 (6. c3 Nge7)) 6. c3 O-O 7.
h3 $5 (7. d4 $5 cxd4 8. cxd4 a6 9. Bxc6 bxc6 10. Nc3 $14) 7... a6 8. Bxc6 $1 (
8. Bf1 e5 9. d3 (9. d4 cxd4 10. cxd4 exd4 11. Nxd4 (11. e5) 11... d5 12. Nxc6
bxc6 13. exd5 Nxd5) 9... d6 10. g3 h6 11. Bg2 Be6) (8. Ba4 b5 9. Bc2 e5 10. d3
d6) 8... bxc6 (8... dxc6 9. d4 (9. d3 $5) 9... cxd4 10. cxd4 Nd7 (10... c5 $1)
11. Nc3 $14 {x Bc8} e5 12. d5 $16 (12. Bg5 $16 Qb6 13. d5 Qxb2 14. Rc1) (12.
Be3 $5 $14 exd4 13. Bxd4 Bxd4 14. Qxd4 Qb6 15. Qd2)) 9. d4 cxd4 10. cxd4 d5 (
10... d6 11. Nc3 Rb8 12. Qc2 $1 Bd7 13. Bf4 $14 Qb6 14. Rab1) 11. e5 Ne4 12.
Nbd2 $1 (12. Be3 $1 $16) (12. Nc3 $1 Nxc3 13. bxc3 Bf5 (13... Qa5 14. Qb3 {
followed by Ba3 or even Qa3!?}) 14. a4 $16) 12... Nxd2 (12... c5 13. dxc5 Nxc5
14. Nb3 Nxb3 15. Qxb3 $14 Be6 16. Nd4) (12... Bf5 13. Nh4 $1 $14) 13. Bxd2 Qb6
14. b4 $3 {This is even better than the computer's 14.Re3. Now Black can just
sit and White while White will improve his position and increase his advantage.
} (14. Re3 $1 {Houdini !} c5 15. dxc5 Qxc5 16. Rc1 Qb6 17. Rb3 Qd8 (17... Qa7
18. Be3) 18. Bg5 $16 (18. Rbc3 $14) 18... Bf5 19. Rb7) 14... Bf5 {Black hopes
to play ...Be4.} (14... Bd7 15. Bc3 $1 Rae8 16. Nd2 Bc8 (16... f6 17. e6 Bc8
18. Nb3 $18 {The pawn on e6 is anything but weak and will be well protected
after Nc5.}) 17. Nb3 Qc7 18. Nc5 $16) 15. Bc3 $3 {The plan is Nd2-Nb3! and
whenever black goes f6 we go e6!!} f6 ({Now} 15... Be4 $6 {makes no longer any
sense due to} 16. Nd2 Bf5 17. Nb3 $16) (15... Rfe8 16. Nd2 f6 17. e6 Qc7 18.
Nb3 Qd6 19. Nc5 $18) 16. e6 $1 Qc7 17. Nd2 Qd6 18. Qe2 g5 19. Nb3 Bg6 20. Nc5
$16 {Black is strategically lost. With her next move she tries to create some
counterchances.} f5 21. a4 f4 (21... a5 22. bxa5) 22. f3 Bf5 23. Nxa6 Rf6 24.
Nc5 Rg6 25. b5 cxb5 (25... h5) 26. axb5 Rb8 27. Ra6 $18 Qd8 28. Rea1 h5 29. Rf1
Kh7 (29... g4 30. fxg4 hxg4 31. hxg4 Bxg4 32. Qd3 $18) 30. Kh1 g4 31. fxg4 hxg4
32. Rxf4 gxh3 33. Qh5+ Bh6 34. Rxf5 hxg2+ 35. Kg1 Qg8 36. Rf7+ Kh8 37. Bd2 1-0

