{a great game by white...study it carfully ! ....black lost almost without a
fight !!} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. c3 Nf6 6. Re1 O-O 7. d4
d5 8. e5 Ne4 9. Bxc6 bxc6 10. Be3 Qb6 11. Qc1 Rb8 12. b3 cxd4 13. cxd4 Bf5 14.
Nc3 Nxc3 15. Qxc3 Rfc8 16. Rec1 a5 17. Bd2 {This is played with the idea that
after ...a4, White has b4 or bxa4 followed by a5.} Ra8 (17... a4 18. b4 (18.
bxa4)) 18. Qe3 f6 (18... Bd7 19. h3 e6 $2 {We already know how to punish this
mistake:} 20. Rc5 $1 {Preventing any counterplay, and if} Bf8 {then simply} (
20... a4 21. b4) 21. Rac1 {, when taking the exchange would lead to a
catastrophe on the dark squares:} Bxc5 22. Rxc5 (22. dxc5 $5) 22... Qd8 23. Qh6
Qf8 24. Qh4 Rab8 25. Bh6 Qe8 26. Qf6 $18) 19. Rc5 Be4 20. Rac1 a4 ({White saw
that after} 20... Bxf3 21. Qxf3 fxe5 22. dxe5 Bxe5 {he can play} 23. Rxc6 $1
Rxc6 24. Qxd5+ $18) 21. b4 Qb7 22. e6 $18 {We know from the previous game that
such a position is strategically winning for White.} g5 23. h4 g4 24. Nh2 h5
25. f3 gxf3 26. gxf3 Bf5 27. Nf1 Kh7 28. Ng3 Bg6 29. Kh1 Qa6 30. Rg1 Rg8 31. b5
cxb5 32. Nxh5 Bxh5 33. Qd3+ Kh8 34. Rxd5 Be8 35. Rg6 f5 36. Qxf5 1-0

