1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. d3 Bg4 $6 {This is dubious but
quite common.} 6. Nbd2 e5 {Black manages to play ...e5 but he has to concede
the pair of bishops.} 7. h3 $1 {Now Black is forced to part with his bishop.} (
{If} 7. Qe2 $2 {then Black gets an acceptable position after} Nd7 8. h3 Be6 9.
b3 Be7 10. Bb2 f6 11. O-O O-O) 7... Bxf3 8. Nxf3 (8. Qxf3 $5 {may be even
better, intending Nc4.}) 8... Nd7 9. O-O Bd6 10. g3 $6 (10. a4 O-O 11. b3 $16)
10... Nf8 11. Kg2 Ne6 12. Be3 O-O 13. Nh4 g6 14. Bh6 Re8 15. Nf3 f6 16. h4 Bf8
