1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. d3 Bg4 6. h3 Bh5 7. b3 $5 {
Not at all forced but interesting!} e6 8. Bb2 $16 Be7 9. Nbd2 O-O (9... a5 {
is simply met with} 10. a4 {stopping any counterplay on the queenside.}) 10.
O-O ({White had a better continuation in} 10. g4 $3 Bg6 11. Qe2 {, starting an
attack on the kingside. White's king feels safe in the centre and keeps the
option to castle queenside.} a5 12. a4 $16) 10... Nd7 (10... a5 11. a4 b5 12.
Qe2) 11. Qe2 $14 f6 12. e5 $2 (12. Qe3 $14) (12. a4 $14) 12... f5 $1 $36 13.
