1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. d3 Bg4 $6 6. h3 Bh5 7. Nc3 ({
I would prefer something like} 7. Nbd2 e6 8. Qe2 Be7 9. g4 Bg6 10. Nc4 $16)
7... Nd7 {Now Black wants to play ...e5, so White prevents it.} 8. g4 Bg6 9.
Bf4 e6 10. Qe2 Be7 11. O-O-O {White castles long, not fearing Black's
counterplay. Black's problem is that his king will be faced with an attack
should he castle kingside.} Qa5 12. Kb1 b5 13. Qe3 b4 14. Ne2 Qb5 15. Ng3 $16 {
[%cal Yh3h4]} a5 16. Nf5 Bf8 17. Bd6 f6 18. d4 O-O-O 19. Ne7+ Bxe7 20. Bxe7
