e6, while if he plays ...e6 himself then White can castle and is ready to
defend d3 with Rd1.} Qd7 (11... e6 12. O-O (12. Bf4 Qd7 13. Rd1) 12... Qd7 13.
Rd1 Nxc4 $2 14. Bg5 $1 $18) 12. a4 $3 {It turns out that Black does not
threaten to take on d3:} ({White is also better after} 12. Be3 $1 Qxd3 13. Qxd3
Rxd3 14. Ke2 Rd7 15. b3 $1 {Black has an extra pawn, but this is where the
good news end. For example} e6 16. Ng5 h6 17. Ne4 $14) 12... Qxd3 $2 13. Ng5 $1
$18) 9... g5 10. Bg3 Qd7 11. Nc3 O-O-O 12. Ne4 Bxf3 13. Qxf3 Qxd3 14. Qxd3 Rxd3
15. b3 $14 {White has good compensation for the pawn.} Rg8 16. Nxc5 Rd4 17. Ke2
