1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {In this lecture we will examine one of Black's
main continuations, the move} e6 (3... Nd4 4. Nxd4 cxd4 5. O-O e6 {leads by
transpostions to 3...e6.}) {After} 4. O-O {Black has essentially only one good
move, which is} Nge7 {. We are also going to cover Black's lesser alternatives
on move four.} 5. d4 {This is our repertoire move. White's strategy is quite
straightforward and he has good chances to gain the advantage.} *

