1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 e6 4. O-O Nge7 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 Qb6 (6... Ng6 7.
Be3 Qc7 8. Be2 Be7 9. c4 O-O 10. Nc3) 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. Bd3 Ng6 9. c4 Be7 10. Nc3
O-O 11. Rb1 Qc7 12. Be3 $14 e5 {A mistake, according to Caruana.} (12... Ne5
13. Be2 {[%cal Yf2f4]}) ({Black should have played} 12... Nf4 {However, White
is still better after for example} 13. Bc2 e5 14. c5 $14) 13. g3 $1 $16 {
Now Black's knight on g6 remains out of play.} d6 14. b4 $1 {White intends
b4-b5, winning control of d5.} Be6 (14... f5 $2 15. exf5 Bxf5 16. Bxf5 Rxf5 17.
b5 $18 {White has a decisive positional advantage.}) 15. Qd2 Rac8 16. b5 Bd8 ({
Black loses the a7-pawn after} 16... cxb5 17. Nxb5 $16) 17. Rfc1 Qd7 18. bxc6
Rxc6 19. Nd5 Bb6 {Black tries to free his game with a pawn sacrifice.} (19...
Bxd5 20. cxd5 Rxc1+ 21. Qxc1 $18 {Transformation of advantages: White has two
strong bishops and a space advantage.}) 20. Nxb6 axb6 21. Bxb6 $16 {Black has
insufficient compensation and Caruana was able to convert his advantage.} Ra8
22. Bf1 Qc8 23. Rb4 Nf8 24. a4 Nd7 25. a5 h6 26. h4 Kh7 27. Qe3 Nc5 28. f4 exf4
29. gxf4 f5 30. exf5 Bxf5 31. Re1 d5 32. cxd5 Rg6+ 33. Kf2 Nd7 34. h5 Rg4 35.
Bh3 Nf6 36. Qc1 Qf8 37. Rc4 Qf7 38. Bxg4 Nxg4+ 39. Kg1 Qxh5 40. Qd2 Qh4 41. Re2
Rf8 42. Rc3 Qh5 43. d6 Rf6 44. d7 Rg6 45. Rg2 1-0

