1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 e6 4. O-O Nge7 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 a6 7. Be2 Nxd4 ({
After} 7... Ng6 {the game can continue with} 8. c4 Qc7 9. Nc3 d6 10. Be3 Be7 (
10... Nxd4 $2 11. Qxd4 {is already extremely uncomfortable for Black since he
cannot develop his kingside without a serious concession.} f6 12. a4 $5 {
I like this best - Black cannot prevent a4-a5.} (12. Na4 $5 $16) (12. Rac1 Be7
13. b4 $16) 12... Be7 13. a5 $16) {Now} 11. Nb3 {is interesting, avoiding the
exchange of pieces - White has more space.} O-O 12. Rc1 Bd7 13. Nd5 exd5 14.
cxd5 Rfe8 (14... Rac8 15. dxc6 Bxc6) 15. dxc6 bxc6) 8. Qxd4 Nc6 9. Qc3 $1 {
Now Black cannot develop his bishop.} b5 10. a4 (10. Bf4 $5) 10... b4 11. Qg3
$14 {Again, Black cannot play ...Be7.} Qf6 (11... Bb7 12. Bg5 $16 (12. Nd2 {
[%cal Yd2c4]}) (12. Bf4) (12. Be3)) 12. Nd2 Bc5 13. Nc4 O-O 14. e5 Qg6 15. Qh3
$1 $16 f6 (15... Qxc2 $4 16. Bd3 $18) 16. exf6 Qxf6 17. Be3 Bd4 18. Bd3 h6 19.
Bxd4 Nxd4 20. Nd6 e5 21. Nxc8 Raxc8 22. Qxd7 Nxc2 23. Qd5+ Qf7 24. Qe4 Qb3 25.
Rac1 Nd4 26. Rxc8 Rxc8 27. f4 1-0

