1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 e6 4. O-O Nge7 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 a6 7. Be2 Nxd4 8.
Qxd4 Nc6 9. Qd2 $5 Be7 10. c4 Qc7 11. Nc3 h5 {This is too much.} ({Logical
would have been} 11... O-O 12. b3 d6 13. Bb2 Bf6 14. Rac1 $14 {White has the
advantage. Black must watch out for Nd5.}) 12. b3 Ne5 13. h3 {Stopping knight
g4.} g5 {An interesting yet very risky strategy. Black tries to attack with
incomplete development.} 14. f4 $1 Bc5+ 15. Kh1 Ng4 16. e5 gxf4 (16... Nf2+ 17.
Rxf2 Bxf2 18. Ne4 $18) 17. Qxf4 Nxe5 18. Ne4 Be7 19. Bb2 d6 20. Bxe5 $18 (20.
c5 $1 {This would have been the move if Bxe5 was not winning.}) 20... dxe5 21.
Qxf7+ Kd8 22. Rad1+ Bd7 23. Qxe6 Qc6 24. Rxd7+ Qxd7 25. Rd1 Qxd1+ 26. Bxd1 Rf8
27. Bf3 Rc8 28. Qd5+ Kc7 29. Qxe5+ Kd7 30. Qxh5 Rcd8 31. Nc5+ Kc8 32. Qg4+ Kb8
33. Nd7+ 1-0

