1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 e6 4. O-O Nge7 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 Qb6 7. Nxc6 bxc6
8. Bd3 Ng6 9. c4 Be7 10. Nc3 O-O 11. Na4 $5 (11. Rb1 $1 {[%cal Yc1e3]}) 11...
Qc7 12. c5 {Fixing Black's strucure. After} d5 13. cxd6 Bxd6 $132 {Black has
an isolated c-pawn but on the other hand he has active piece play.} 14. g3 c5 (
14... e5 $2 {would be very bad strategically:} 15. Be3 Bh3 16. Re1 Rfd8 17. Qc2
$16 {Black has a weak c-pawn while his knight on g6 remains misplaced.}) 15.
Be3 Ne5 16. Be2 Bb7 (16... c4 $1 $132) 17. Rc1 $14 Bxe4 $6 18. Nxc5 $1 Bc6 19.
f4 $1 Ng6 $2 20. Ne4 $1 Rfd8 21. Qc2 $1 Bxe4 22. Qxe4 $16 {After some
inaccuracies by Black White has gained a clear advantage - the pair of bishops
in an open position.} Qa5 23. f5 Qe5 24. Bf3 Qxb2 25. fxg6 hxg6 26. Qc2 Qa3 27.
Qc3 1-0

