exd4 (7... O-O 8. Nc3 (8. d5 $16) 8... a6 9. Bxc6 Nxc6 10. dxe5 Bxe5 {
Unfortunately for Black he has to take with the bishop.} 11. Nxe5 Nxe5 12. Qd6
$18 {White has a decisive positional advantage due to the weak spuares in
Black's position. A possible continuation:} (12. Bf4) (12. f4 {is also
possible but in my opinion unnecessary.}) 12... Nc4 (12... Nc6 13. Bf4 {
is even worse as Black will never be able to remove the queen from d6.}) 13.
Qd4 b5 14. b3 Nb6 15. Ba3 Re8 16. Bd6 {Black can hardly breath.}) 8. Nxd4 O-O
9. Nc3 Qc7 10. Nf3 a6 11. Ba4 (11. Be2 $16) 11... Ne5 12. h3 b5 13. Bb3 Bb7 14.
