20. Nxf4 Bxf4 21. Nd5 Bxd5 22. Bxd5 {A typical situation with opposite
coloured bishops. White has a big advantage since his bishop is much stronger.}
Rc8 23. g3 Be5 24. h4 Qb6 25. hxg5 g6 26. Qh3 Rc2 27. Rac1 Rxb2 28. Qxd7 Kg7
29. Rc6 Qd4 30. Qe7 a5 31. Rxg6+ Kxg6 32. Qxf8 Qa7 33. Qh6# 1-0

