Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. c3 Nf6 6. Re1 O-O 7. h3 d5 $6 {A typical mistake,
Black has mixed up the 6.h3 and 6.d4 lines. The problem is Black doesn't have
Ne4 after a natural e5 because of d3. While if we played d4 before, this would
be completely okay for Black.} 8. e5 Ne8 9. d4 {This leads to a good space
advantage for White. In this section, we will see games on how to play in
these structures.} *

