{[%evp 0,47,33,6,69,32,35,37,74,41,41,52,41,8,23,0,11,20,20,20,20,20,48,54,45,
26,31,30,64,52,65,75,74,80,73,97,99,64,96,96,135,98,165,204,211,162,165,175,
183,582]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. Re1 Nf6 6. h3 (6. c3 {
is our move instead, anyway we transpose.}) 6... O-O 7. c3 d5 $2 {a common
mistake played by a strong fide master.} 8. e5 Ne8 {The problem is Black can't
play Ne4, as always because of d3.} 9. d4 cxd4 (9... a6 10. Bxc6 bxc6 11. dxc5
Nc7 12. Be3 Ne6 13. Nbd2 {White is simply a pawn up.}) 10. cxd4 Bd7 11. Nc3 Nc7
12. Bf1 $5 b5 13. Be3 Na5 14. b3 $1 {White is stabalizing and he has a big
space advantage.} Rc8 15. Qd2 b4 16. Ne2 Nc6 17. Nf4 a5 18. Rac1 Na7 19. Rc5
Bb5 20. Rec1 Qd7 21. Qc2 Ne6 22. Nxe6 fxe6 23. Bxb5 Qxb5 24. Rxc8 1-0

