{[%evp 0,16,26,14,44,44,44,35,35,35,28,11,15,1,-3,-11,0,-13,-4] In the part 2
of the Rossolimo g6 variation, we are going to cover the 7.d4 variation and
discuss a lot of games related to it.} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7
5. c3 Nf6 6. Re1 O-O 7. d4 (7. h3 {In the previous lecture, we discussed this
variation which doesn't require theory and can be played by hand, just by
knowing the middlegames plans.}) 7... d5 8. e5 Ne4 {Usually, we reach this
structure where Black has his Knight on e4 and we have little bit more space
in the center. Black can also choose to capture the pawn on d4 now or later.
Our main idea is to capture on c6 and take advantage of the weak c6-pawn or in
some cases trade the e4-knight and launch a kingside attack with moves like
Bg5-Qd2.} *

