{[%evp 0,21,26,14,44,44,44,41,42,43,33,10,15,-7,-3,-11,1,7,-26,0,-3,-71,-25,
-41]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. c3 Nf6 6. Re1 O-O 7. d4 d5 8.
e5 Ne4 9. Bxc6 bxc6 10. Be3 cxd4 11. cxd4 {In this section, we are going to
see model games where we try to exploit the backward c6-pawn and completely
dominate the key c5-square. One of the key ideas is to trade the e4-Knight
with Nfd2-Qxd2, keep the b3-Knight on c3 and followed by Na4-Nc5. You will see
more of such in the modelgames.} *

