1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. c3 Nf6 6. Re1 O-O 7. d4 d5 8. e5
Ne4 9. Bxc6 bxc6 10. Be3 cxd4 (10... Qb6 {Black is trying to generate some
counterplay against the b2-pawn.} 11. Qc1 Rb8 12. b3 Qa5 {Black's plan is to
stop Nd2 due to Qxc3 and threaten Rb3 now.} 13. dxc5 Rxb3 14. axb3 Qxa1 15. b4
Qa4 16. Nbd2 $16 {White is fighting for the advantage.}) 11. cxd4 Qb6 12. Qc1
a5 (12... Bg4 13. h3 Bxf3 14. gxf3 {traps the Knight.}) (12... Bf5 13. Nc3 {
White is better.}) 13. Nc3 Nxc3 14. Qxc3 Bf5 15. b3 Rfb8 16. Nd2 h5 17. h3 Rc8
18. Rac1 Bf8 19. a3 {The typical plan in such positions.} Rab8 (19... e6 20.
Qb2 c5 {cant be played.} 21. dxc5 Bxc5 22. Rxc5 Rxc5 23. b4 {wins material.})
20. Qb2 Qd8 21. Rc3 Qd7 22. Rec1 f6 23. Rc5 Rb5 24. a4 Rxc5 25. Rxc5 Bxh3 26.
gxh3 Qxh3 27. Nf1 fxe5 28. dxe5 Bg7 29. Qd4 Qe6 30. Rxa5 Bxe5 31. Qh4 Rf8 32.
Ra7 Bd6 33. b4 Rf3 34. Ra8+ Kf7 35. Bh6 Qe2 36. Rf8+ Ke6 37. Rxf3 Qxf3 38. Be3
Kd7 39. a5 Kc8 40. Bc5 Bf4 41. Qxe7 Qg4+ 42. Ng3 Bxg3 43. fxg3 Qxg3+ 44. Kf1
Qd3+ 45. Kf2 Qd2+ 46. Kf3 Qd1+ 47. Kf4 Qg4+ 48. Ke5 Qe4+ 49. Kf6 Qxe7+ 50. Kxe7
h4 51. Kd6 h3 52. Bg1 d4 53. Kxc6 d3 54. a6 Kb8 55. b5 d2 56. a7+ Ka8 57. b6
1-0

