1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Nf6 5. Re1 Bg7 6. c3 O-O 7. d4 d5 8. e5
Ne4 9. Bxc6 bxc6 10. Be3 Rb8 (10... Bg4 {This is never an option because,
Black's Knight gets trapped after gxf3.} 11. h3 Bxf3 12. gxf3 $18) 11. Qc1 f6 (
11... Qb6 12. b3 cxd4 13. cxd4 Bf5 (13... Bg4 14. h3 {Black has wasted one
tempo.}) 14. Nc3 Nxc3 15. Qxc3 Rfc8 16. Rac1 e6 17. Nd2 Bf8 18. Bg5 Ba3 19. Qe3
Bxc1 20. Rxc1 {White has good control of the c5-square.}) 12. Nbd2 fxe5 (12...
Qb6 {trying to keep some pressure.} 13. b3 fxe5 14. Nxe5 Bxe5 15. dxe5 Nxc3 16.
Qxc3 d4 17. Qc4+ {Bg5 next.}) 13. Nxe5 Nxd2 (13... Bxe5 14. dxe5 Nxd2 15. Qxd2
Qb6 16. b3 (16. b4 d4 {is complex.}) 16... Be6 17. Rac1 {followed by b4.}) (
13... cxd4 14. Nxc6 (14. cxd4 Bxe5 15. dxe5 Nxd2 16. Qxd2) 14... dxe3) 14. Qxd2
cxd4 15. Bxd4 Qc7 16. Nd3 (16. b4 {fixing up is also possible.}) 16... Bf5 17.
Bxg7 Kxg7 18. Nc5 Rbe8 (18... e5 {gives up the exchange.} 19. Na6 Qd6 20. Nxb8
Rxb8 21. Qe3 {Black has little compensation for the exchange, which is not
enough.}) 19. f4 Kg8 (19... e5 {Black is trying to open the position.} 20. Rxe5
Rxe5 21. Qd4 Rfe8 22. Re1 Be4 23. Nxe4 dxe4 24. fxe5 {White is better.} (24.
Rxe4 c5 {Black has played a trick on us!})) 20. Re5 Qb6 21. b4 a5 22. a3 Rf7
23. Rae1 axb4 24. axb4 Qa7 25. h3 $1 Bc8 26. Qe3 Qa3 27. Kh2 Qb2 28. Qd4 Qa3
29. R1e3 Qc1 30. b5 cxb5 31. Qxd5 e6 32. Qc6 Ref8 33. Nxe6 Bxe6 34. Qxe6 Qf1
35. Rf3 Qc4 36. Qxc4 bxc4 37. Kg3 Rc7 38. Rfe3 Rf6 39. Rd5 Kg7 40. Re4 Rfc6 41.
Rdd4 h5 42. Kf3 Kf6 43. g3 Kf7 44. Ke3 Kf6 45. Rd8 Kf7 46. Kd4 Ra6 47. Kd5 Rac6
48. Rh8 Rc5+ 49. Kd4 Kg7 50. Rhe8 R5c6 51. R8e7+ Rxe7 52. Rxe7+ Kf6 53. Re5 h4
54. gxh4 Rc8 55. h5 Rh8 56. hxg6 Rh4 57. Re4 Rxh3 58. Kxc4 Kxg6 59. Rd4 Rh8 60.
Kb5 Rb8+ 61. Kc4 Kf5 62. Kd3 Rb1 63. Kc2 Rb8 64. c4 Ke6 65. Kc3 Rc8 66. Rd5 Rh8
67. f5+ Kf6 68. c5 Rh4 69. c6 Ke7 70. Rd7+ Ke8 71. Rd4 Rh1 72. Kc4 Rf1 73. Rd5
