Nf6 6. Re1 O-O 7. d4 {The other option covered in previous lesson is 7.h3.} d5
8. e5 Ne4 9. Be3 (9. Bxc6 {I usually prefer to capture on c6 first and then
Be3.}) 9... cxd4 10. cxd4 Qb6 11. Bxc6 bxc6 (11... Qxb2 {Is not possible.} 12.
Bxd5 {White will have good compensation.}) (11... Qxc6 12. Nfd2 {Amazing move!
We want to trade the Knights and keep our other Knight on c3.} Nxd2 13. Qxd2
Be6 14. Nc3 {with a good position.}) 12. Qc1 Rb8 13. b3 Bd7 14. Nc3 Nxc3 15.
Qxc3 f6 {creating some pressure but also creates weakness for itself.} 16. Rac1
Bg4 17. Qxc6 Qxc6 18. Rxc6 Bxf3 19. gxf3 fxe5 20. dxe5 Bxe5 21. Bxa7 Ra8 22.
Bc5 Bd6 23. Bxd6 exd6 24. a4 Rxf3 25. Re3 Rf6 26. Rb6 Kf7 27. Rb7+ Kg8 28. Ree7
