{[%evp 0,15,26,14,44,44,44,36,36,42,31,8,36,28,19,17,23,26]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3
Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. c3 e5 6. d4 {In this section, we are going to see
model games arriving after this intresting gambit variation. Our aim is to
sacrifice the pawn for quick developement.} (6. d3 {Is also possible,
intending Be3-d4.}) 6... cxd4 7. cxd4 exd4 8. Bf4 {Our main ideas are to keep
the Bishop on d6, one Bishop on c4 and create threats against Black's King and
underdeveloped pieces.} *

