1. e4 $1 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. c3 e5 6. d4 {A very tricky
gambit!} (6. d3 Nge7 7. Be3 {usual theory.}) 6... cxd4 (6... exd4 7. cxd4 Nxd4
8. Nc3 {We can also take on d4, but this move is also intresting.}) 7. cxd4
exd4 (7... Nxd4 8. Nxd4 exd4 9. Bf4 Ne7 (9... Qb6 10. Na3 Ne7 11. Nc4 {White
is winning.}) 10. Na3 O-O 11. Bd6 {complete domination.}) 8. Bf4 Nge7 (8... Qb6
9. Na3 a6 10. Nc4 {Once again the same trick.}) (8... d6 9. Nxd4 {simply wins
the pawn. Next up is Nc3-Nd5.}) 9. Bd6 O-O 10. Nbd2 (10. a4 $5 a6 11. Bc4 Na5 (
11... b6 12. Nbd2 Bb7 13. b4 Re8 14. Bxf7+ Kxf7 15. Ng5+ Kf8 16. Qb3 {with
mate to follow.}) 12. Ba2 Re8 13. Ng5 {with full domination.}) 10... a6 11. Bd3
b6 (11... b5 {also possible.} 12. Rc1 Bb7 13. e5 {intending Ne4, Qd2 and so on.
}) 12. a3 Bb7 13. Bc4 $1 (13. h3 {Black wants to play Re8-Nc8, if we are slow
with such moves.} Re8 14. Rc1 Nc8 15. Bf4 d6 $15 {with good position.}) 13...
Na5 (13... Re8 {loses to the specatular} 14. Bxf7+ Kxf7 15. Qb3+ Kf8 16. Ng5 {
with checkmate to follow.}) 14. Ba2 Bc6 15. b4 Nb7 16. Be5 $1 Bxe5 17. Nxe5 Bb5
18. Re1 $18 Qc7 19. Ndf3 $1 Qd6 20. Ng4 $3 d3 21. e5 Qc7 22. Rc1 $1 Qd8 23. a4
$1 Bc6 24. Nd4 $1 $18 Nd5 $2 25. Bxd5 1-0

